premise_source_doc_sentence: Mediterraneo is a 1991 Italian film that won the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film in 1991 .
The film is set during World War II , and regards a group of Italian soldiers who become stranded on a Greek island and are left behind by the war .
The filming took place on the Greek island of Kastellórizo , in the Dodecanese island complex .
The film was a success at the box office .
